so the faction mail will look something like this (i will send it to wgw leader and bw leader so they can faction mail this too):

Faction event: Title-suggestion competition!

Hello Wolverines! its time to renrew our faction titles! (you know, the ones you have beside your name in the INFO tab i.e Poobah, Lord executioner, Grand Poobah etc)
and since we are too lazy to come up with some on my own, we have decided to let you guys do the work for prizes!
so here's the deal - send a suggestion containing new titles for all 4 levels of our faction ranks as follows: 

Tier 1– Default position new members get when first joining our ranks.

Tier 2– Position members earn after lasting 100 days in the faction.

Tier 3– Position members earn after lasting 1000 days in the faction and/or OC managers. Ability to send newsletters and manage OC’s.

Tier 4- Junior leadership position for council members.

Tier 5- Leadershit, Self explanatory (this one was vetoed by kap, so cant change this one)

Rules: 

1. feel free to be wild and as creative as you can be but no curses etc, torn has a code too.
2. send all suggestions to ForesterISR [2529142] no later than Deceber 10th (send Chronology [290441] a copy too, he doesnt need one, but its a decent chance to spam him)
3. 1 entry per person
4. the winners will be picked by our council and junior alumni in a vote held after we get shitfaced in the parking lot.
5. we will use only the winner titles, but there will be 2nd place and 3rd place.

Prizes:
1st - 40m
2nd - 25m
3rd - 15m
4th - bwahaha

Good luck to all!

Once our new recruitment thread is up and running I think it would be a neat idea to run weekly competitions to encourage our members to bump it. 
We could offer a 3 x 5m reward chosen randomly every week for 3 of the players who've bumped the thread in the past week. 
1 bump = 1 entry
Unlimited entries (must not break Torn spamming rules)
3 winners chosen every Sunday
Should be a pretty easy and cheap way to engage our members
We'll send it out as soon as the recruitment thread is done

@WR Leadership @WR Council 

Guys. I want to run some competitions during this training break to keep people on their toes, motivated and interested. I want each GW lead/council member (that has time) to think of, and run 1 competition. Prizes are optional - I don’t want every comp to be about prize money so there doesn’t have to be a prize. But each competition should be structured in a way that’s fun, and encourages player engagement. Historically we’ve run baking competitions, guess the member comps, battle stat races - all to great effect. 

What say thee? 

Please react with a ✅ if you can run a competition or a ❌ if you can’t.
